The paper deals with generating 3D animation of humans from 2D videos using deep learning, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as person detection and segmentation, depth map estimation, and human pose tracking. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with graphics (GR) as it involves generating 3D animations. Additionally, the paper involves multimedia (MM) as it deals with processing video data. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG).
